# Item Special Effects — Primary Dictionary

**Do NOT overwrite or regress this file.** `src/constants/item-special-effects.ts` is the canonical source for all item effects attachable to rare/epic armors and other items.

## Structure

Each effect has:
- **name** — Effect box label (displayed as header)
- **description** — Effect box body (displayed below name)
- **bonuses** — Optional flat stat enhancements (+4 DEX, +10 AWR). Always shown in Bonuses box. Never scale.
- **immunities** — Optional (stun, panic, suppression, burning)
- **incapChanceMultiplier** — Optional (e.g. 1.6 for Relentless)
- **durationReduction** — Optional (stun, panic, suppression, burning, blind)

## When Adding Effects

1. Add to `ITEM_SPECIAL_EFFECTS` with unique id
2. Add id to `ItemSpecialEffectId` union type
3. Wire armor/items to use it via `specialEffect` property

## Do NOT

- Remove or rename existing effects without updating all consumers
- Change the file structure (name, description, bonuses)
- Duplicate effect definitions elsewhere
